#compdef tdx
# =============================================================================
# tdx — Niklas Heer's "Your todos, in markdown, done
#          fast" — a single-binary Go TUI + scriptable
#          CLI todo manager that stores tasks as plain
#          GitHub-Flavored Markdown checkbox items
#          (`- [ ]` / `- [x]`) inside an ordinary
#          `todo.md` file the user can version-control,
#          edit in their preferred text editor, or pipe
#          through any other Markdown tooling.  Built
#          around yuin/goldmark for CommonMark + GFM
#          task-list parsing + writing.
#          Distinguishing from Taskwarrior (Paul
#          Beckingham's flat-file UNIX-philosophy task
#          manager with .taskrc + .data binary format —
#          NOT markdown-native), Todoist CLI (commercial
#          + cloud-dependent), Bullet Journal apps,
#          Logseq (graph-based notes — heavier than
#          flat todo.md), and the official Obsidian
#          Tasks plugin (requires Obsidian desktop app
#          + Electron runtime) by:
#            - MARKDOWN-NATIVE STORAGE — every todo is
#              a `- [ ] text` line in a plain `.md`
#              file; the entire file is human-readable
#              + git-diffable; users can edit the file
#              with $EDITOR + tdx will reactively pick
#              up the changes; no proprietary serialization
#            - GOLDMARK PARSING + WRITING — uses
#              yuin/goldmark v1.7 (this is the headline
#              CLI library that CONTINUES Axis 42 on
#              the Go side; see taxonomy notes below)
#              to parse the markdown file into an AST,
#              traverse task-list-item nodes, mutate
#              their CheckboxState (Unchecked /
#              Checked), and serialize back to disk
#              preserving formatting + non-task content
#              (headings, paragraphs, code blocks)
#            - YAML FRONTMATTER PER-FILE CONFIG — each
#              `todo.md` can carry its own YAML
#              frontmatter (`---\nfilter_done: true\n
#              show_headings: false\n---`) overriding
#              the global config for that file; useful
#              for project-specific defaults
#            - FAST + SMALL — single 4 MB statically-
#              linked Go binary; instant startup; the
#              project claims "30-40x faster than
#              alternatives" (presumably against
#              Taskwarrior / Todoist-CLI / mdtt)
#            - VIM-STYLE NAVIGATION — `j`/`k` for next/
#              prev, `5j` for relative-jump-five, number
#              keys for direct positional jumps; muscle
#              memory transfer for vim users
#            - HELIX-STYLE COMMAND PALETTE — `:` opens
#              an in-TUI command palette with fuzzy
#              search (à la Helix editor + many modern
#              IDE command palettes); commands
#              discoverable without memorizing keys
#            - INTERACTIVE TUI MODE (default invocation)
#              — toggle / create / edit / delete / undo
#              / move / copy / read-only-toggle / check-
#              all / uncheck-all / filter-done from
#              keybindings; built on charmbracelet/
#              bubbletea or equivalent (this is the
#              corpus Axis 28 TUI library family)
#            - SCRIPTABLE CLI MODE — `tdx list`, `tdx
#              add "text"`, `tdx toggle <idx>`, `tdx
#              edit <idx> "text"`, `tdx delete <idx>` —
#              non-TUI subcommands suitable for shell
#              scripts + git hooks + CI integration
#            - READ-ONLY MODE — `-r` / `--read-only`
#              flag prevents auto-save; useful for
#              previewing a teammate's todo.md without
#              risk of accidentally toggling
#            - SHOW HEADINGS — `--show-headings`
#              displays Markdown `#` / `##` / `###`
#              section headers between groups of
#              todos, preserving the document's
#              organizational structure
#            - MAX VISIBLE LIMIT — `-m N` / `--max-
#              visible N` caps the visible-at-once
#              count; useful for very long todo files
#              where the user only wants to focus on
#              the top N
#            - SMART CONFLICT DETECTION — when external
#              changes to todo.md occur during a tdx
#              session (e.g. another editor saves the
#              file), tdx detects + attempts auto-
#              merge; reactive filesystem watching via
#              fsnotify
#            - RECENT FILES — `tdx recent` lists
#              recently-opened todo files; `tdx recent
#              N` jumps directly to file #N; `tdx
#              recent clear` clears the recent history;
#              cursor position restored on reopen
#            - LAST FILE — `tdx last` opens the most-
#              recently-used file
#            - CROSS-PLATFORM — pre-built binaries for
#              macOS arm64/amd64, Linux amd64/arm64,
#              Windows amd64; published via Homebrew
#              tap (`brew install niklas-heer/tap/tdx`)
#              + curl-install script + GitHub Releases
#            - 57+ STARS ON niklas-heer/tdx — smaller
#              than the Obsidian-tier projects but
#              steadily growing; active engineering
#              under regular release cadence
#          Used by: developers tracking todo lists
#          inside their dotfiles repo or project repo
#          (the todo.md sits next to README.md), git-
#          first workflows that benefit from diffable
#          todo history, terminal-purists who want a
#          TUI alternative to GUI task managers, and
#          script writers needing programmatic todo
#          manipulation from CI / cron / hooks.
#
# Author:  Niklas Heer (niklas-heer on GitHub;
#          https://nheer.com); Engineering Manager at
#          Tradebyte (Ansbach, Germany); founder of
#          @dev-night community.
# Source:  https://github.com/niklas-heer/tdx
#          https://github.com/niklas-heer/tdx/blob/main/cmd/tdx/main.go
#          https://github.com/niklas-heer/tdx/blob/main/internal/cmd/cli.go
#          https://github.com/niklas-heer/tdx/blob/main/go.mod
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `tdx --help` shows
#          the option list + subcommand summary; full
#          docs in repo README.md.
# Library: github.com/yuin/goldmark v1.7.13 — Yusuke
#          Inuzuka's "A markdown parser written in Go.
#          Easy to extend, standard (CommonMark)
#          compliant, well structured."  This is the
#          headline dependency for this completion's
#          axis-42 continuation role; see taxonomy
#          notes below.  Also charmbracelet/bubbletea
#          + charmbracelet/lipgloss (Axis 28 TUI
#          framework), fsnotify for reactive file
#          watching, gopkg.in/yaml.v3 for YAML
#          frontmatter parsing.
# License: MIT
# Status:  57+ stars on niklas-heer/tdx; active
#          development (latest commit 2026-05-26);
#          Go 1.25+ required; published as homebrew
#          tap niklas-heer/tap/tdx.
#
