#   * tdx (R758 THIS) — Niklas Heer's todo manager
#     with goldmark v1.7.13 as direct dep; 57 stars
#     but pure markdown-tasklist use case
#   * mdblog (broqiang) — Chinese markdown blog with
#     goldmark + highlighting + meta; 363 stars but
#     Chinese-language UI may limit international
#     adoption
#   * gh-eco — gh CLI extension; uses goldmark but
#     INDIRECT (transitive via glamour)
#   * gopher-code (ProjectBarks) — Claude Code Go
#     port; 1052 stars; uses goldmark INDIRECTLY
#   * crd-wizard (pehlicd) — K8s CRD wizard; uses
#     goldmark INDIRECTLY (via glamour)
#   * hugo (gohugoio/hugo) — would be ideal but
#     already in corpus as `_hugo`
#   * deck (ajstarks) — already in corpus
#   * bearer (Bearer/bearer) — already in corpus
#
# tdx is the chosen Axis 42 Go-side continuation
# because:
#   - It uses yuin/goldmark v1.7.13 as a DIRECT
#     dependency in go.mod (not indirect like most
#     other CLIs that pull in goldmark only via
#     charmbracelet/glamour)
#   - The todo-list use case exercises goldmark's
#     TaskList extension specifically — the headline
#     feature for checkbox parsing
#   - It is a clean, focused single-purpose CLI
#     (not a giant framework like Hugo)
#   - It is the closest functional analog to basalt
#     (R757) — both are markdown-first TUIs that
#     read+render+edit `.md` files using their
#     language's canonical markdown parser
#   - 57 stars is modest but the author is
#     actively engineering with regular CI + coverage
#     tracking + Homebrew distribution; not an
#     abandoned weekend project
#
